exp_info.label: Sample Sources & Incubation Temperature
exp_info.description: Specify samples and temperatures to run an experiment at.

media_well_strings.label: Media Wells
media_well_strings.description: Specify wells to be used as media blanks as comma-separated humanized well indices. Leave blank if you would prefer to use the default Strateos media blanks.

inoc_info.label: Inoculation Parameters
inoc_info.description: Select culture and media volumes for inoculation

inc_time_1.label: Initial Outgrowth Time
inc_time_1.description: Select the incubation time, must be between 8 and 24.

recovery_info.label: Recovery Parameters
recovery_info.description: Select culture and media volumes for recovery

options.value: M9 Minimal Media w 50mg per L TRP
options.name: modified_m9_media_with_50mg_per_l_trp

inc_time_2.label: Recovery Incubation Time
inc_time_2.description: Select the incubation time, must be between 1 and 12.

induction_info.label: Induction Parameters
induction_info.description: Select culture and media volumes for induction loops

induction_time.label: Induction Timing
induction_time.description: Specify total induction duration and at what interval to sample at.

sample_points.label: Sampling Times
sample_points.description: Specify a comma-separated list of integers, representing hours to sample at. A maximum of 6 can be specified.

induction_plate_info.label: Induction Plate Info
induction_plate_info.description: Specify whether to create a new induction plate each cycle or use existing plate.

options.name: Create New Induction Plate Each Cycle

induction_reagents.description: Specify base media and inducer to be used.
induction_reagents.label: Induction Reagents

ind_cult_vol.label: Culture Volume
ind_cult_vol.description: Specify volume of culture from preceding plate to transfer into each new induction plate.

options.value: M9 Minimal Media w 50mg per L TRP
options.name: modified_m9_media_with_50mg_per_l_trp

media_vol.label: Media Volume
media_vol.description: Specify volume of media for induction plate.

inducer.label: Select Inducer
inducer.description: Choose inducer from inventory to use. Aliquot must have a `concentration` property associated with it.

inducer_conc.label: Inducer Concentration
inducer_conc.description: Concentration of inducer to use in all wells in a plate. Last column (12) will be without inducer.

inducer_unit.label: Concentration Units
inducer_unit.description: Specify units of concentration for inducer

inducer_unit.label: Concentration Units
inducer_unit.description: Specify units of concentration for inducer

col_num.label: Column Number
col_num.description: Specify column number for this ethanol concentration (1-indexed)

sampling_info.label: Measurement Plate Parameters
sampling_info.description: Specify volume, solvent, and stain for read and flow

read_solv.label: Plate Read Solvent
read_solv.description: Select Solvent to Dilute Cells in for Plate Read

flow_solv.label: Flow Solvent
flow_solv.description: Select Solvent to Resuspend Cells in for Flow

stain_before_flow.label: Stain Prior to Flow
stain_before_flow.description: Choose whether to stain cells prior to flow

save_for_rnaseq.label: Save Plates for RNA Seq
save_for_rnaseq.description: Choose whether to save a plate of cells for sequencing

skip_first_flow.label: Skip First Induction Plate Flow
skip_first_flow.description: Choose whether to omit first induction timepoint from flow

only_endpoint_flow.label: Only Endpoint Flow
only_endpoint_flow.description: Specifies to only run a single flow plate at end of induction period.

read_each_recovery.label: Plate Read Each Recovery
read_each_recovery.description: Choose whether to read a plate at the end of each recovery loop

read_each_induction.label: Plate Read Each Induction
read_each_induction.description: Choose whether to read a plate at the end of each induction cycle.

validate_samples.label: Validate Samples Contain ID
validate_samples.description: Validates each source sample has a `sd2_common_name` or `sbh_uri` property.

experiment_id.label: Experiment ID
experiment_id.description: Experimental Request ID to be associated with data generated.
